struct India {
    var ImageArr = ["Coimbatore","Goa","Statue of Unity","Kashmir","Ladakh","Manali","Ooty","Vrindavan"]
    var ImageNameArr = ["Adiyogi Shiva Statue","Goa","Statue of Unity","Kashmir","Ladakh","Manali","Ooty","Prem Mandir"]
    var ImageDescriptionArr = ["The Adiyogi Shiva statue is a 112-foot tall bust of the Hindu deity Shiva. It is made of steel and weighs around 500 tons. The statue is located in Coimbatore, Tamil Nadu, India, in the foothills of the Velliagiri mountains. Some say the statue is an iconic inspiration for people and is not a deity or temple. Others say it is a place for meditation and experiencing the scenic beauty of nature and enjoy the light show.","Goa, a tiny emerald on the west coast of India, with its natural Scenic beauty, abundant greenery, attractive beaches, historical temples and churches, colourful feasts and festivals, and above all warm and hospitable people with a rich cultural milieu, has today emerged as an ideal tourist destination worldwide.","The Statue of Unity is a 182-meter-tall monument dedicated to Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel, a statesman and leader of India. It's located on Sadhu-Bet Island in the Narmada River, about 3.5 kilometers downstream from the Sardar Sarovar Dam. The statue is a tribute to Patel, also known as the 'Iron Man of India'.The viewing gallery is located at a height of 153 meters and offers a view of the Sardar Sarovar.","Kashmir is known for its pristine natural beauty. It's a valley between the Great Himalayan range and the Pir Panjal mountain range. The region has a different climate for every region due to the variation in altitude. Kashmir is often called “Paradise on Earth” due to its lush green valleys, snow-capped mountains, beautiful lakes, & picturesque landscapes.","Ladakh is most famous for breathtaking landscapes, the crystal clear skies, the highest mountain passes, thrilling & fun adventure activities, Buddhist Monasteries and festivals.The climate of Ladakh is cold and dry. Average annual precipitation is roughly 3 inches (80 mm); fine, dry, flaked snow is frequent and sometimes falls heavily.","Manali is a hill station in the Kullu district of Himachal Pradesh, India. It's located at the northern end of the Kullu Valley, which was formed by the Beas River.Manali is known for its natural charm, beautiful views, snow-capped mountains, and lush forests. It's also a popular destination for honeymooners.","Ooty, also known as Udhagamandalam, is a hill station in Tamil Nadu, India. It's known as and is located at an altitude of 7,350 feet (2,240 meters) above sea level.Ooty is surrounded by the Nilgiri Mountains, which are part of the Western Ghats. The town is known for its beautiful scenery, including lush valleys, rolling hills, lakes, forests, and tea gardens.","Prem Mandir is a Hindu temple in Vrindavan, Mathura, India. It is maintained by Jagadguru Kripalu Parishat, an international non-profit, educational, spiritual, charitable trust. The complex is on a 54-acre site on the outskirts of Vrindavan, and is dedicated to Lord Radha Krishna and Sita Ram."]
    var ImageLocation = ["diyogi Shiva Statue, Tamilnadu.","Goa, Maharashtra.","Statue of unity, Sardar Sarovar Dam, Gujarat.","Jammu and kashmir.","Ladakh, Great Himalayas, Jammu & Kashmir.","Manali, Himachal Pradesh.","Ooty, Tamilnadu.","Prem Mandir, Vrindavan, Utter Pradesh."]
}


struct Canada {
    var ImageArr = ["Banff Gondala-Canada","Chateau des charmes winery-Canada","CN Tower-Canada","Old-quebec-Canada","Stanley Park-Canada","The Butchart Gardens-Canada","Toronto-Canada","Vancouver-Canada"]
    var ImageNameArr = ["Banff Gondala","Chateau des charmes","CN Tower","Old Quebec","Stanley Park","Butchart Gardens","Toronto","Vancouver"]
    var ImageDescriptionArr = ["The sense of anticipation inside your gondola cabin changes as quickly as the view when the Banff Gondola swoops you up above the treetops. For eight minutes, you’ll glide steadily upwards over what feels like an impossibly steep mountainside. Then, 700 metres in elevation gain later, find yourself on the summit of Sulphur Mountain high above the town of Banff. From here, the alpine is yours to discover with vantage points of six different mountain ranges.","Chateau des Charmes was founded in 1978 by Paul Bosc, a fifth generation French winegrower. Paul and his young family arrived in Niagara with the idea that growing our own grapes was the best way to make fine wine. Paul did what no other in Niagara-on-the-Lake had done before, he planted Canada’s first commercial vineyard dedicated exclusively to vitis vinifera, the European grape varieties that make the finest wines.","The CN Tower is a 553.3 meter concrete communications and observation tower in downtown Toronto, Canada. It's the tallest free-standing structure in the western hemisphere and one of Toronto's most popular attractions. The tower was built on land reclaimed from Lake Ontario in 1973 to solve broadcasting problems and demonstrate Canadian industry. The name ‘CN’ refers to Canadian National, the railway company that built the tower.","Old Quebec is a historic district in Quebec City, Canada. It's a walled city that was designated a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 1985. The area is divided into two parts: the Upper Town and the Lower Town. The Upper Town is on top of Cap Diamant and is protected by ramparts, a citadel, and other defensive structures. The Lower Town developed around Place Royale and the harbor.According to official data, 85 per cent of the population there is Catholic.","Stanley Park is a magnificent green oasis in the midst of the urban landscape of Vancouver. Explore the 400-hectare natural West Coast rainforest and enjoy scenic views of water, mountains, sky, and majestic trees along Stanley Park's famous Seawall.Stanley Park is a 400-hectare (1,000-acre) park in Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada. It's one of the largest urban green spaces in North America.","Butchart Gardens National Historic Site of Canada is an internationally-known public attraction that has been open to visitors since 1904. It is located on the Saanich Peninsula, approximately 21 kilometres north of Victoria, British Columbia. The gardens occupy the site of a former quarry and borders on Tod Inlet.The gardens are located on the Saanich Peninsula, about 21 kilometers north of Victoria on Vancouver Island.","Toronto is Canada's largest city and a world leader in business, finance, technology, entertainment and culture. Its large population of immigrants from all over the globe has also made Toronto one of the most multicultural cities in the world.Toronto is Canada's largest city and the capital of Ontario. It's also the fourth largest city in North America.Toronto is known for being a global leader in business, finance, technology, entertainment, and culture.","The City of Vancouver is a coastal, seaport city on the mainland of British Columbia. Located on the western half of the Burrard Peninsula, Vancouver is bounded to the north by English Bay and the Burrard Inlet and to the south by the Fraser River.Vancouver is a modern city in British Columbia, Canada. It's the largest city in the province, with a population of over 630,000 and a metro area population of over 2 million."]
    var ImageLocation = ["Banff Gondola, Banff, Canada.","Chateau des charmes, Davids, Canada.","CN Tower, downtown Toronto, Canada.","Old Quebec, Quebec City, Canada","Stanley Park, downtown Vancouver, Canada.","Butchart Gardens, Brentwood Bay, Canada.","Toronto, Ontario, Canada.","Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada."]
}


struct Australia {
    var ImageArr = ["Adelaide-Australia","Brisbane-Australia","Cairns-Australia","Canberra-Australia","Gold Coast-Australia","Melbourne-Australia","Perth-Australia","Sydney-Australia"]
    var ImageNameArr = ["Adelaide","Brisbane","Cairns","Canberra","Gold Coast","Melbourne","Perth","Sydney"]
    var ImageDescriptionArr = ["Adelaide is the capital of South Australia and the fifth most populated city in Australia. It's located in the southeast of South Australia, from the Barossa Valley in the north to the Fleurieu Peninsula in the south.With beautiful hills, white sandy beaches and enticing wine districts, Adelaide has the best of everything. Adelaide is regarded as wine and the food capital of Australia and has more restaurants per head than any other major Australian city.","Brisbane is a major centre of research and innovation in the Asia-Pacific, particularly in medicine and biotechnology. A transport hub, Brisbane is served by large rail, bus and ferry networks, as well as Brisbane Airport and the Port of Brisbane, Australia's third-largest seaport.Brisbane is the capital of Queensland and Australia's third-largest city. It's a coastal metropolitan area known for its subtropical lifestyle, outdoor dining, and friendly locals.","Cairns is the only place in Australia where two UNESCO World Heritage Sites are located side-by-side. It's the gateway to the Great Barrier Reef, Daintree and Wet Tropics rainforest, Atherton Tablelands and the outback Savannah region.There are multiple matches for Cairns, including a pile of stones and a city in Queensland. Cairns may also refer to Cairns, Queensland, a tropical destination that is surrounded by the rainforest and reef.","Canberra is the capital city of Australia, it's located in the Australian Capital Territory (ACT), surrounded by New South Wales (NSW). With a population of over 350 million people, it is Australia's largest inland city and the eighth-largest city overall.Canberra is known for its mix of history, art, and the outdoors. It has well-known museums and historical sites, as well as brewpubs, hidden gems, quiet nature, and family-friendly attractions.","The Gold Coast is one of Australia's premier holiday destinations. Famous for its surf breaks, stunning beaches, theme parks, shopping, nightlife and hinterland, it has been attracting Australian families for many decades.The Gold Coast is a holiday destination in Queensland, Australia. It's known for its beaches, surfing, theme parks, nightlife, and rainforest. The Gold Coast is Australia's sixth-largest city, with over 635,000 residents.","Melbourne is the capital city of Victoria, and Australia's second-largest city. Focused around a central city, Greater Melbourne's area of approximately 9900 km of suburbs spread more than 40 km to the south, 30 km to the east, 20 km to the north and sprawl across vast, flat basalt plains to the west.Melbourne is Australia's second-largest city and the capital of Victoria. It's known for its vibrant arts scene, stunning architecture, and coffee culture.","Perth is the capital of Western Australia and the fourth most populated city in Australia. It's located on the Swan River, 1,324 miles from Adelaide, 1,648 miles from Darwin, and 1,691 miles from Melbourne.Perth lies along the estuary of the Swan River, 12 miles  above that river's mouth, which forms the inner harbour of neighbouring Fremantle. The  centre of a metropolitan area containing about three-fourths of the state's population.","Sydney is the largest and most populous city in Australia and the state capital of New South Wales. Sydney is located on Australia's south-east coast of the Tasman Sea. Inhabitants of Sydney are called Sydneysiders, comprising a cosmopolitan and international population of people from numerous places around the world.It's the capital of New South Wales and is known for its harbor, beaches, bays, and national parks."]
    var ImageLocation = ["Adelaide, South Australia.","Brisbane, capital of Queensland, Australia.","Cairns, Queensland, Australia.","Canberra, Capital Territory, Australia.","Gold Coast, southeastern Queensland, Australia.","Melbourne, southeastern coast, Australia.","Perth, Western Australia.","Sydney, south-east coast, Australia."]
}


struct USA {
    var ImageArr = ["Boston-USA","Chicago-USA","Disney World-USA","Puerto Rico","Las Vegas-USA","New Orleans-USA","New York-USA","Statue of Liberty-USA"]
    var ImageNameArr = ["Boston","Chicago","Disney World","Puerto Rico","Las Vegas","New Orleans","New York","Statue of Liberty"]
    var ImageDescriptionArr = ["Boston  is the capital and largest city of the state of Massachusetts (officially theCommonwealth of Massachusetts), in the United States. Boston also serves as county seat of the state's Suffolk County. Boston played a key role in the American Revolution in the late 1700s. The Boston Tea Party took place in 1773 when colonists dumped tea into the Boston Harbor to protest British taxation.Boston is known for its diverse culinary scene.","The City of Chicago covers an area of 60,000 hectares and sits 176 meters (578 feet) above sea level on the southwestern shore of Lake Michigan. At 190 km wide and 495 km long, its the 5th largest body of fresh water in the world.Chicago is also home to the Chicago River, a canal that connects Lake Michigan and the Mississippi River. The Chicago River is the only river that flows backwards.","Walt Disney World, also known as ‘Walt Disney World Resort’ or ‘Disney World,’ is a vacation destination complex that includes theme parks, water parks, hotels, restaurants, shopping, golf courses, and other entertainment venues. It's located in Lake Buena Vista, Florida and is about the size of San Francisco.Explore six lands of enchantment, one-of-a-kind attractions and magic here at the place where storybook fantasy becomes everyday reality.","Puerto Rico is a self-governing island commonwealth in the West Indies. It's made up of a main island, four smaller islands, and hundreds of cays and islets. The island is 100 miles long and 35 miles wide, and has a tropical climate with little seasonal variation. Puerto Rico is the easternmost island in the Greater Antilles chain. It's located 50 miles east of the Dominican Republic and 40 miles west of the Virgin Islands.","Las Vegas is a sprawling neon-washed city in the sunny desert state of Nevada. Rightly known as the City of Lights, it has a dazzling array of luxurious casinos, mega-hotels, and plush resorts. Buzzing bars and live shows ensures the fun never stops after sunset.Las Vegas is a large, glitzy city in the desert surrounded by mountains. It's full of neon lights, casinos, hotels, resorts, bars, live shows, and natural wonders.","New Orleans is offbeat, unusual, loud and proud - all part of the gumbo that has simmered for 300 years. A city in a class of its own, New Orleans offers endless opportunities for fun and entertainment, casting a global allure that brings more than 17 million visitors to the city a year.Founded by the French, ruled by the Spanish for 40 years, and purchased by the United States in 1803. The city was the site of significant battles in the War of 1812 and the Civil War.","New York City (NYC) is the most populated city in the United States and is located in the southern tip of New York State. It's a major financial and cultural center and is home to some of the world's largest buildings.The city is made up of five boroughs: Brooklyn, the Bronx, Manhattan, Queens, and Staten Island. It's home to 8.4 million people who speak more than 200 languages and come from all over the world.","The Statue of Liberty is a 305-foot (93-meter) statue located on Liberty Island in New York Harbor. The statue is made of copper sheets supported by an iron framework and weighs 62,000 pounds. The statue's green color comes from the copper sheets.The Statue of Liberty, a hollow colossus composed of thinly pounded copper sheets over a steel framework, stands on an island at the entrance to New York Harbor."]
    var ImageLocation = ["Boston, Massachusetts, USA","Chicago, Illinois, USA.","Disney World, Florida, USA.","Puerto Rico, Territory, USA.","Las Vegas, Nevada, USA.","New Orleans, Louisiana, USA.","New York, New York City, USA.","Statue of Liberty, New York on Liberty Island, USA."]
}


struct UAE {
    var ImageArr = ["Abu Dhabi-UAE","Bruj Khalifa-UAE","Dubai desert safari-UAE","Dubai Frame-UAE","Gigantic Moon hotel-UAE","Burj Al Arab","Museum of the Future-UAE","Palm Jumeirah"]
    var ImageNameArr = ["Abu Dhabi","Burj Khalifa","Dubai desert safari","Dubai Frame","Gigantic Moon hotel","Burj Al Arab","Museum of the Future","Palm Jumeirah"]
    var ImageDescriptionArr = ["Abu Dhabi is the capital of the United Arab Emirates (UAE) and the largest emirate by size and GDP contribution. It's located on the Arabian Gulf coast and is bordered by the Sultanate of Oman, the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia, and the emirate of Dubai.Abu Dhabi is made up of 200 islands and has a diverse landscape, including beaches, desert scenery, and world-famous attractions.Abu Dhabi is known for being a city of entertainment.","The Burj Khalifa is the tallest building in the world and a global icon. Truly a feat of engineering, the building represents the conceptual heart and soul of the city of Dubai. At 828m tall, this magnificent structure is located next to Dubai Mall and has drawn visitors from all over the world since opening in 2010.The Burj Khalifa's structural system is a ‘buttressed core’ made of high-performance concrete wall construction.","A desert safari involves a jeep drive through enormous mounds of sand (called ‘dune-bashing’), and a stop at a campsite where you'll have the opportunity to ride camels, get henna tattoos and be entertained by a belly dancer during dinner.Desert safaris are popular in Dubai due to its beautiful deserts and weather conditions. Safaris usually start in the afternoon around 3:30 PM and end in the evening around 9:00 PM.","It holds the record for the largest frame in the world. The building has a height of 150.24 meters and a width of 95.53 meters. The building mainly serves as an observatory, providing views of old Dubai in the north and newer parts in the south.Some say the Dubai Frame is a beautiful structure with fun activities inside, a symbolic building in an ideal location, and a nice place to have a general view of the city.","Each sphere will be a 360-degree recreation of the moon on a grand scale, complete with realistic-looking craters and texture. Each recreated moon could tower 735 feet high (224 meters) with a 2,042 foot circumference, depending on location and planning permissions.The Moon is a proposed 224-meter-high spherical resort that would include a moon-like experience. It would be built in four locations around the world, including Dubai.","The Burj Al Arab is a 1,053-foot tall hotel in Dubai. It's the world's tallest all-suite hotel, standing on an artificial island 920 feet off the beach. The Burj Al Arab is designed to resemble the sail of an Arabian dhow, a type of boat.The Burj Al Arab is a 7-star hotel with 28 double-story floors, 202 suites, nine restaurants, a spa, kids' club, private beach, three swimming pools, and a helipad. The shape of the structure is designed to resemble the sail of a ship.","The Museum of the Future is a torus-shaped building in Dubai, United Arab Emirates. It opened on February 22, 2022, and is a landmark dedicated to innovative and futuristic ideologies.The museum explores how society could evolve in the coming decades using science and technology. It's a place where people of all ages can see, touch, and shape our shared future. Bringing researchers, designers, inventors, and financiers together.","Palm Jumeirah was the first of the artificial islands off the coast of Dubai to be built. Shaped like a huge palm tree, it added 56 kilometers to Dubai's coastline. Palm Jumeirah includes a trunk with 17 fronds surrounded by a crescent-shaped breakwater.Palm Jumeirah is made up of artificial archipelagos built from reclaimed land. It's part of a larger series of developments called the Palm Islands."]
    var ImageLocation = ["Abu Dhabi, the capital of the UAE.","Burj Khalifa, skyscraper in Dubai, UAE.","Dubai desert safari, Dubai, UAE.","Dubai Frame, Zabeel Park, Dubai, UAE","Gigantic Moon hotel, Dubai, UAE","Burj Al Arab, Dubai, UAE.","Museum of the Future, Dubai, UAE.","Palm Jumeirah, Island in Dubai, UAE"]
}

